<section class="section">
  <p class="small muted"><a href="/vocations/">← Back to Vocations</a></p>
  <h2>FORMATION HOUSES</h2>
  <div class="line"></div>
  <p class="lede">The Thailand Province maintains formation houses corresponding to each stage of the path to Religious life &mdash; from the youngest Aspirant to the Brother preparing for perpetual profession.</p>

  <h3 style="margin-top:36px">THE HOUSES OF FORMATION</h3>
  <div class="line"></div>
  <div class="card-grid">
    <div class="card">
      <h3>JUNIORATE</h3>
      <div class="meta">Aspirancy &middot; first introduction</div>
      <p>The house where the youngest candidates are accompanied through their initial growth in the spiritual life, while continuing their formal education.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>POSTULATE</h3>
      <div class="meta">Postulancy &middot; preparing for the Novitiate</div>
      <p>A focused period of living the Brothers' daily rhythm and discerning, with the formators, readiness to enter the canonical year of Novitiate.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>NOVITIATE</h3>
      <div class="meta">The canonical year of formation</div>
      <p>The house where the Novice spends a year set apart for prayer, study of the Rule, and deep discernment &mdash; before pronouncing first vows.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>SCHOLASTICATE</h3>
      <div class="meta">Studies and apostolic preparation</div>
      <p>The house where the Brother in temporary vows pursues theological and pastoral formation, preparing for perpetual profession and apostolic ministry.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <blockquote class="callout">
    Each formation house is, above all, a place of prayer &mdash; where young men learn to listen to the Lord in silence, in community, and in the writings of Saint Louis-Marie de Montfort.
  </blockquote>

  <p class="small muted" style="margin-top:24px">A directory of each formation house, with its address and the Brother formators in charge, is being prepared with the Commission on Formation.</p>
</section>

